definitions.definition: A historical region of central Italy , in which the city of Rome was founded and grew to be the capital city of the Roman Empire.
Lazio : A modern administrative region of central Italy .

main_definition: ( historical ) A historical region of central Italy , in which the city of Rome was founded and grew to be the capital city of the Roman Empire.
